      <h2>How to legally increase your take-home pay</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contribute to 401k:</strong> Reduces federal and state taxable income</li>
        <li><strong>Use an HSA:</strong> Triple tax advantage — pre-tax contributions, tax-free growth, tax-free withdrawals for medical</li>
        <li><strong>Review W-4 withholding:</strong> Many Americans over-withhold — update your W-4 to get more money each paycheck</li>
        <li><strong>Live in a no-tax state:</strong> Moving from California to Texas saves $3,000–$10,000/year at $65K salary</li>
        <li><strong>Use Dependent Care FSA:</strong> Up to $5,000 pre-tax for childcare expenses</li>
      </ul>

